                            <comment id="193445" author="adilger" created="Tue, 25 Apr 2017 20:57:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think &quot;sync&quot; will affect the inode counts on the ldiskfs MDS, since they are not cached by the clients.  All file creates are done immediately on the MDS so &quot;lfs df -i&quot; should always be accurate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
